NAME
    Media::Info::Mediainfo - Return information on media file/URL, using the
    `mediainfo` program

VERSION
    This document describes version 0.003 of Media::Info::Mediainfo (from
    Perl distribution Media-Info-Mediainfo), released on 2017-07-10.

SYNOPSIS
    Use directly:

     use Media::Info::Mediainfo qw(get_media_info);
     my $res = get_media_info(media => '/home/steven/celine.avi');

    or use via Media::Info.

    Sample result:

     [
       200,
       "OK",
       {
         audio_bitrate => 128000,
         audio_format  => "aac",
         audio_rate    => 44100,
         duration      => 2081.25,
       },
       {
         "func.raw_output" => "General\nComplete name   ...",
       },
     ]

FUNCTIONS
  get_media_info
    Usage:

     get_media_info(%args) -> [status, msg, result, meta]

    Return information on media file/URL, using the `mediainfo` program.

    This function is not exported by default, but exportable.

    Arguments ('*' denotes required arguments):

    *   media* => *str*

        Media file.

    Returns an enveloped result (an array).

    First element (status) is an integer containing HTTP status code (200
    means OK, 4xx caller error, 5xx function error). Second element (msg) is
    a string containing error message, or 'OK' if status is 200. Third
    element (result) is optional, the actual result. Fourth element (meta)
    is called result metadata and is optional, a hash that contains extra
    information.

    Return value: (any)

